The paper discusses the business value of recommender systems, which are commonly used in e-commerce and social media websites. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with the retrieval of information from large datasets. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category, as recommender systems may have implications for data privacy and security. The paper also discusses the challenges of measuring the business value of recommender systems in practice, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Software Engineering (cs.SD) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, as it discusses the user experience and performance assessment of recommendation algorithms.
